title: Art Institute of Chicago Puzzle Cube
description:
This puzzle is developed using six masterpieces from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection: Claude Monet’s Water Lilies, 1906; Georges Seurat’s A Sunday on La Grande Jatte—1884, 1884/86;  Gustave Caillebotte’s Paris Street; Rainy Day, 1877;  Grant Wood’s American Gothic, 1930; Vincent van Gogh’s The Bedroom, 1889; and Pierre-Auguste Renoir’s Two Sisters (On the Terrace), 1881.

This magic folding cube featuring six images, one per side. The cube is made up of eight small cubes. These can be opened and refolded, to mix up images and then return them to their original state.

  • Dimensions: 2.22 x 2.22 x 2.22 in. (when closed)
  • Printed fold-out with information.
  • Six images.
